The paper deals with machine learning algorithms for disease progression modeling using longitudinal data, specifically for Alzheimer's disease using volumetric MRI biomarkers. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of MRI biomarkers suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
